4
00:00:16,040 --> 00:00:17,800
The music students are hosting
a jazz showcase, right?

5
00:00:17,920 --> 00:00:19,360
But my friends want me to be the vocalist.

6
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:20,400
I don't want to.

7
00:00:20,920 --> 00:00:22,540
I'll be there in the crowd.

8
00:00:22,880 --> 00:00:24,960
I'll be in the very front row,

9
00:00:25,940 --> 00:00:27,480
the very same spot where I fell for you.

10
00:00:27,520 --> 00:00:29,240
I want to ask you one question.

11
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,480
How about we start dating?

12
00:00:30,920 --> 00:00:32,340
I never gave up on you, you know?

13
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:34,360
But when I'm with you,

14
00:00:34,520 --> 00:00:36,440
it feels like
someone else already has your heart.

15
00:00:39,320 --> 00:00:40,080
I choose you.

16
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:42,440
You're not the only one
who feels this way.

17
00:00:42,480 --> 00:00:44,240
Now I feel the same way about you

18
00:00:44,600 --> 00:00:46,040
as you do about me.

19
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:51,160
As for the large-scale artworks
that will be displayed at the jazz showcase...

20
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:52,920
Yes?

21
00:00:52,960 --> 00:00:54,680
We're creating large-scale artworks
for the College of Music?

22
00:00:54,960 --> 00:00:56,040
Correct!

23
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:59,560
So that means I might get to be
a part of this showcase with him.

24
00:01:00,240 --> 00:01:01,240
Something like that.

25
00:01:01,960 --> 00:01:04,400
Only once in a while
do the music students ask for our help,

26
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:06,240
so we have to do our best.

27
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:09,120
Therefore, we're gonna pick a leader

28
00:01:09,160 --> 00:01:10,080
and dive right into work.

29
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:11,920
Duang, you do it.

30
00:01:12,039 --> 00:01:13,039
No way.

31
00:01:13,160 --> 00:01:13,840
What?

32
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,560
Qin's part of the showcase.

33
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:18,080
If I were a leader,
I wouldn't get to see him at all.

34
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:20,320
Jeez, you're so whiny.

35
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:22,200
Right, anyone
who wants to be the leader,

36
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:23,720
step up to the front.

37
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:37,800
What...

38
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:08,800
Wow!

39
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:10,720
Duang, you want to be the leader?

40
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:15,520
Go on, Duang. You're amazing.

41
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:16,280
Alright,

42
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:19,440
- so it's settled. Duang's the leader.
- We're counting on you, Duang.

43
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:22,120
I barely have any time, though.

44
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:23,360
Gosh, it's not gonna take long.

45
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:24,480
Only 2-3 days.

46
00:02:24,780 --> 00:02:26,480
Bro, you need to do it.

47
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:28,840
Qin's gonna get to see you shine, you know?

48
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:32,280
True, I wouldn't want it to be anyone else.

49
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:34,200
True!!

50
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:36,640
Okay, please give it up
to the new leader of the project!

51
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,560
Duang, you're the best.

52
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:03,560
♫I'm not leaving soon, so bear with me♫

53
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:08,700
♫Wherever you are
is where I'll always be♫

54
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:12,600
♫Wherever you go,
I'll find you eventually♫

55
00:03:12,640 --> 00:03:14,920
♫You may push me away, but I won't flee♫

56
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:17,960
♫Who would you love if it weren't me?♫

57
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:20,240
♫So, wanna make a deal, maybe?♫

58
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:22,640
♫Alright, alright, don't worry♫

59
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:24,920
♫Just date me first, take it easy♫

60
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:27,320
♫I'll be so cute you'll fall naturally♫

61
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:29,640
♫No matter what,
you'll always run into me♫

62
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:32,040
♫Okay, okay, let it be♫

63
00:03:32,079 --> 00:03:34,360
♫I know you're also into me,♫

64
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:36,880
♫Don't you feel the same? I can see♫

65
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:43,160
♫I'll keep on flirting,
don't try to avoid me♫

66
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:47,960
♫'Cause I won't stop
till you fall for me♫

67
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:52,520
♫I'll keep on flirting,
I won't stop, I guarantee♫

68
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:58,960
♫I'll love you hard,
and once you say yes, I'll set you free♫

69
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:22,520
Jeez,

70
00:04:23,420 --> 00:04:25,160
you're not letting me
get my Qin energy.

71
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:27,400
I could wipe it off myself, couldn't I?

72
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:33,920
Oh, after this evening,
I'll be really busy,

73
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:36,720
and I wouldn't be able
to meet you for a few days.

74
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:37,520
Mm.

75
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:40,960
You...

76
00:04:41,180 --> 00:04:41,900
Hm?

77
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:44,200
What am I gonna do?

78
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:46,380
I'll probably miss you so much

79
00:04:46,590 --> 00:04:48,800
that I'll die for sure.

80
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,040
Why are you being so whiny?

81
00:04:53,140 --> 00:04:55,720
Well, I'm not gonna see you at all.

82
00:04:58,640 --> 00:04:59,920
But what you draw

83
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:02,600
will stand behind me when I'm onstage.

84
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,600
Plus, I have my own practices, too.

85
00:05:11,860 --> 00:05:12,860
Yeah, you're right.

86
00:05:14,220 --> 00:05:15,880
Then I'll work so hard

87
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:18,000
that my artworks will drop so many jaws!

88
00:05:19,380 --> 00:05:20,200
Who the hell are you talking to?

89
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:23,320
Let's just eat more cake.

90
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:24,680
Come on.

91
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:29,160
Nom...

92
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:31,000
Big bite.

93
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:34,360
You're adorable.

94
00:05:34,580 --> 00:05:36,280
Can you stop being so cute?

95
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:40,840
I forgot.

96
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:42,440
You can't stop it

97
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:45,159
since it's the way you are.

98
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:47,840
Big bite.

99
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:58,780
Give me that.

100
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:00,760
I can eat it myself.

101
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:24,160
You want a bite?

102
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,280
Fine, I'll feed myself.

103
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:44,680
Few, View, help Jamie scrub that off

104
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:46,800
since that one barely shows up to class.

105
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,800
His brain's not really braining.

106
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:50,720
Sike!

107
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,880
The rest of you, come here.

108
00:06:53,180 --> 00:06:53,920
So...

109
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:55,840
I think we should have
a little meeting here

110
00:06:55,880 --> 00:06:57,320
because we'll have
to be divided into groups.

111
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,480
Please help Pae.

112
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:01,360
We'll make
some multi-faceted boxes like so.

113
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,840
I think I'll handle this one.

114
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:05,200
Alright, go ahead
and divide up the work

115
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:07,160
since this is gonna be...

116
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:09,160
View.

117
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:11,320
So...I'm gonna take
a quick bathroom break.

118
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:13,680
Take care of this for me.

119
00:07:22,960 --> 00:07:25,360
Are you at the condo?
Can I come over?

120
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:30,800
Of course.

121
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:50,000
[I'll go draw now;
good luck with your practice]

122
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,000
[Just send a text if you miss me,
and I'll be on my way to yaa]

123
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:52,400
My practice is gonna run late tonight.

124
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:09,440
Here.

125
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:24,600
What do we have here, my friend?

126
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,240
Right,

127
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:27,960
I got it.

128
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:30,520
Duang's been pulled away, huh?

129
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:32,640
Mm,

130
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:35,679
he's working with his classmates.

131
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,039
I guess he's busy.

132
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,480
So how does it feel

133
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:41,080
to finally be the one who waits?

134
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,000
Tormenting?

135
00:08:48,860 --> 00:08:49,860
Hey, what's up?

136
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,000
What are you guys talking about?

137
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:56,520
Someone here is realizing
how much of a torture it is to wait.

138
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:58,240
Huh?

139
00:08:58,920 --> 00:08:59,840
The heck do you mean?

140
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:00,680
Hey, wait.

141
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:03,800
Time to rehearse.

142
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,080
Ready?

143
00:09:19,420 --> 00:09:20,020
Mm.

144
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:05,840
Boo!

145
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,080
Hey,

146
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:09,920
it's dark outside.

147
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:11,160
Let's grab something to eat.

148
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:12,640
Mm, let's.

149
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:15,160
Any nice places to eat around here?

150
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:17,800
What do you feel like having?

151
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:19,080
Anything is fine.

152
00:10:20,100 --> 00:10:21,360
Give me some recommendations.

153
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:24,520
I don't know many restaurants.

154
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:25,880
I'm more familiar with bars.

155
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:27,920
I can tell!

156
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:31,800
All my seniors are talking about you.

157
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,960
Cutie this, cutie that.

158
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:35,760
That much?

159
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:38,400
Don't act so surprised.

160
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:56,640
Hey...

161
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:59,000
can we not eat
somewhere around the university?

162
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:01,000
I don't want any friends to spot me.

163
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:04,120
Wait, isn't that a good thing?

164
00:11:06,360 --> 00:11:07,640
Well, I bailed on them.

165
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:09,760
I ditched work for you.

166
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:11,360
I don't want them to tease me, either.

167
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:13,520
They don't want me
to be in a relationship.

168
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:17,840
Is it bad that everyone says

169
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:19,880
you're my boyfriend?

170
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:24,560
Well...it's not like that.

171
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:26,920
But we're not boyfriends.

172
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:29,800
Who says?

173
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:32,160
Marvis.

174
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:34,680
I know that.

175
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:36,200
I'm not falling in love.

176
00:11:36,390 --> 00:11:37,720
Alrighty,

177
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:39,360
me neither.

178
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:52,640
That's it for me.

179
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:53,480
Sure thing.

180
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,400
What drink is this?

181
00:11:57,760 --> 00:11:58,960
I really can't read it.

182
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:01,120
It's, "Chrysanthemum tea."

183
00:12:02,380 --> 00:12:03,120
Mum...

184
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:04,880
Like mommy?

185
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:09,080
No. Don't just mix up words.

186
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:12,000
It's the name of a Thai herbal tea.

187
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:17,680
I'll get iced pink milk.

188
00:12:19,740 --> 00:12:21,560
Look at you

189
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:23,400
asking all those questions

190
00:12:23,440 --> 00:12:24,960
and still going with what feels safest.

191
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,040
I'm just not sure if it's good or not.

192
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:29,520
If not, you can trade with mine.

193
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,680
Then, we'll get

194
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:35,560
one chrysanthemum tea
and one iced pink milk.

195
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:37,200
- Of course.
- Thank you.

196
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:48,760
Excuse me,

197
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,120
are you guys a couple?

198
00:12:57,520 --> 00:12:58,720
Is there anything you want?

199
00:12:59,160 --> 00:13:01,200
If you're not a couple,

200
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:03,320
may I have your Instagram?

201
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:07,400
Oopsie...

202
00:13:08,160 --> 00:13:09,160
My bad.

203
00:13:12,880 --> 00:13:14,400
We're not a couple.

204
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:16,640
No! We totally aren't.

205
00:13:19,100 --> 00:13:20,560
But I won't give you my Instagram.

206
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:32,960
Alright.

207
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:40,200
Buh-bye.

208
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:56,120
The color is uncanny.

209
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:58,840
It's so yellow
that it hurts your eyes.

210
00:13:59,320 --> 00:14:00,840
Why would it hurt my eyes?

211
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,080
Never mind.

212
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:05,720
Want a sip?

213
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:25,960
It's good, isn't it?

214
00:14:26,220 --> 00:14:28,520
It's very sweet,

215
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:30,400
but I'm into it.

216
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:34,480
Knew it.

217
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:46,040
Good thing you didn't give
that guy your Instagram.

218
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:48,120
Judging from his looks,
he's definitely a player.

219
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:49,360
He's not making the cut.

220
00:14:49,760 --> 00:14:50,440
Huh?

221
00:14:52,560 --> 00:14:54,040
I just don't like his guts.

222
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:55,300
He looks like a player.

223
00:14:55,340 --> 00:14:56,800
Even I can tell.

224
00:14:57,360 --> 00:14:58,720
It's fine, anyway.

225
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:00,760
It's not gonna be serious.

226
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:02,760
It's not fine.

227
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:04,280
He's definitely not making the cut.

228
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:05,640
It's a no from me.

229
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,200
Then, who's gonna make the cut?

230
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,560
No one.

231
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:15,360
Possessive much?

232
00:15:20,480 --> 00:15:22,040
What? Are you just gonna go silent?

233
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:24,000
I'm not possessive.

234
00:15:24,520 --> 00:15:26,120
Mm, I got it.

235
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:29,840
It's called being protective.

236
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:32,400
Okay...

237
00:15:32,920 --> 00:15:34,920
Whatever you say.

238
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:07,260
Pae,

239
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:09,040
scrape it nice and smooth

240
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:10,880
- so that it can be drawn on beautifully.
- I know.

241
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:11,960
- Good.
- Jeez...

242
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:13,800
I shouldn't have let you be the leader.

243
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:16,240
Uh, friends...

244
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:17,480
Proad and Prach,

245
00:16:17,520 --> 00:16:18,800
do you mind speeding up the work for me?

246
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:20,080
- Oh, sure, sure.
- Alright, thank you.

247
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:23,280
Whoa, friends!

248
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:24,600
Tew, my friend.

249
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:27,440
You need a saxophone
and some stars on it.

250
00:16:27,680 --> 00:16:28,800
Right, thank you so much.

251
00:16:30,120 --> 00:16:31,120
Whoa...

252
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:32,520
Aom,

253
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:34,640
that's the cutest.

254
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:35,880
Amazing job.

255
00:16:35,920 --> 00:16:36,680
Come here.

256
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:37,440
Ooh!

257
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:39,920
Why are you pulling on me?
I need to finish my work!

258
00:16:40,180 --> 00:16:41,560
Unfinished work is one thing,

259
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,120
you walking relentlessly is another!

260
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:45,360
Look, you're giving me a headache.

261
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,800
Wait, I have that inhaler.

262
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:50,400
Here.

263
00:16:51,040 --> 00:16:51,680
Look.

264
00:16:58,080 --> 00:16:59,720
Cute and practical.

265
00:17:00,080 --> 00:17:02,280
Everyone and their mother
has this banger.

266
00:17:05,079 --> 00:17:06,760
Get this, you can do this with them.

267
00:17:07,920 --> 00:17:08,640
Look.

268
00:17:12,780 --> 00:17:14,960
Inhalers assembled into lightning

269
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,000
from DUMBLE INHALER V2!

270
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:17,880
Hold up.

271
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:19,760
I didn't pull you aside for this.

272
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:21,720
I was gonna tell you
to pump the brakes, bastard!

273
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:23,200
The work is not that urgent.

274
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:26,119
But it is urgent!

275
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:27,240
Urgent, my ass.

276
00:17:27,280 --> 00:17:28,280
There are still two days left.

277
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:29,520
Come on now,

278
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:31,200
just get it done tonight.

279
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:32,120
And don't you slack off.

280
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:33,560
Come help Pae and me over there.

281
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:35,400
I'm off.

282
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:38,080
Are you a superhuman?

283
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:39,040
You're gonna drop in your tracks.

284
00:17:39,080 --> 00:17:40,640
Whatever.
Are you gonna come help me now?

285
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:41,520
Fine!

286
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,040
What...

287
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:46,200
Bastard, you took my inhaler!

288
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:48,200
Duang!

289
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:50,840
- Give it to me.
- Here.

290
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:53,710
♫Let's go♫

291
00:17:53,750 --> 00:17:57,120
♫Boom, boom, boom, boom, boom, boom♫

292
00:17:57,320 --> 00:18:00,470
♫To love is to take you by surprise♫

293
00:18:00,650 --> 00:18:02,750
♫Boom, boom, boom♫

294
00:18:03,210 --> 00:18:06,280
♫True love has no match against you♫

295
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:07,150
♫Go!♫

296
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:25,640
Pae,

297
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:27,360
look at Duang.

298
00:18:29,280 --> 00:18:31,400
Goddammit, he's rushing it.

299
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:39,800
Whoa! Duang, stop.

300
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:43,440
If you paint with that brush,
you're gonna have to redo the whole thing.

301
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:45,840
What?

302
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:48,120
Right, my bad.

303
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:49,120
Forgot to take a look.

304
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:08,760
Hello?

305
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:12,120
Sorry to bother,

306
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:13,800
but we need you here to see Duang.

307
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,760
He's listening to literally no one.

308
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:18,000
He's in low-battery mode.

309
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:19,240
Please take him to get some sleep.

310
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:20,560
I'll even bow down if you want.

311
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:22,040
What's going on with him?

312
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:25,200
He's being so stubborn
and pushing his limits to work.

313
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:26,320
I'm afraid he's gonna drop dead.

314
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:27,640
What is he doing?

315
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:31,000
Giving orders and helping friends.

316
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:32,600
At first, he was just drawing outlines,

317
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:34,120
but he's basically
doing almost everyone's work now.

318
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:35,520
Please just get him to bed.

319
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:37,040
Where are you guys? I'm on my way.

320
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:39,200
Right in front of the faculty building.

321
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:40,400
But the artworks are almost done

322
00:19:40,840 --> 00:19:42,080
because he's rushing everything.

323
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:43,360
He doesn't know his limits at all.

324
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:06,800
Duang, stop right there.

325
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:10,000
You've had too much caffeine already.

326
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:12,560
Yeah, does your dad
own coffee production?

327
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:14,240
It's none of your business!

328
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:16,280
I can drink however much coffee I want.

329
00:20:35,560 --> 00:20:36,760
Oh, you're still here!

330
00:20:37,320 --> 00:20:38,320
Aw...

331
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:42,120
I'm not imagining things, am I?

332
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:43,680
Is this real?

333
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:45,120
It's real.

334
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:47,560
I miss you so much.

335
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:49,680
I'm so happy you came to see me.

336
00:20:53,160 --> 00:20:54,560
How many cups of coffee did you have?

337
00:20:58,800 --> 00:21:00,560
Aren't you afraid you'll go into shock?

338
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:04,200
- You're worried about me...
- Eat.

339
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:07,560
- But my work is...
- Gonna eat,

340
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,200
or go back to the condo?

341
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:13,520
Eating is fine.

342
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:29,040
Finally, we can get some rest.

343
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:31,480
Off he goes.

344
00:21:38,800 --> 00:21:40,320
Do you think it's okay
for you to work this hard?

345
00:21:41,380 --> 00:21:42,680
Why do you have
to push yourself this much?

346
00:21:43,960 --> 00:21:46,120
I just want to get things done quickly

347
00:21:46,420 --> 00:21:48,080
so that I can see you.

348
00:21:49,720 --> 00:21:50,920
Are you kidding me?

349
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:53,320
Do you know any limits?

350
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:57,480
Whenever I have to pull
an all-nighter, I do it at my own place

351
00:21:57,680 --> 00:21:59,160
so that I can fall asleep whenever I want.

352
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:01,160
But this...

353
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:02,800
What if you collapse?

354
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:08,640
Do you think I'm delighted

355
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:11,160
to see you sick?

356
00:22:19,080 --> 00:22:20,080
Why the fuck are you smiling?

357
00:22:23,360 --> 00:22:24,120
Well...

358
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:28,120
Just stop being so cute.

359
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:38,520
Okay, then.

360
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:41,560
I'll listen to every word you say.

361
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:44,280
I'm not gonna overwork

362
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:47,680
or drink too much coffee anymore.

363
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:19,480
Well, well, well,

364
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:21,160
look at him acting all unstoppable

365
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:23,120
but ending up here.

366
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:30,640
Qin, please take him to the condo.

367
00:25:31,760 --> 00:25:32,960
As for the rest,

368
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:34,280
I'll handle it.

369
00:25:35,640 --> 00:25:37,280
Mm, I'll do it now.

370
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:39,200
Right, Qin.

371
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:43,160
Don't tell him
that I asked you to pick him up.

372
00:25:57,640 --> 00:25:58,520
Duang...

373
00:26:00,040 --> 00:26:01,720
Duang, wake up.

374
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:13,280
Come on, let's go back to my place.

375
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:17,400
Hey...

376
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:19,200
just let me help my friends
with the paint buckets...

377
00:26:19,240 --> 00:26:20,720
Get some rest, Duang.

378
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:26,840
It's time to rest.

379
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:29,600
You've been doing this
since the other night.

380
00:26:37,560 --> 00:26:38,560
But I haven't...

381
00:26:38,600 --> 00:26:39,480
Don't be stubborn.

382
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:44,040
Qin,

383
00:26:45,480 --> 00:26:47,000
please listen and don't judge.

384
00:26:47,800 --> 00:26:49,520
I don't think
Duang's gonna eat that anymore.

385
00:26:51,120 --> 00:26:52,240
Like, I'm hungry.

386
00:26:54,160 --> 00:26:55,760
Mm, go ahead.

387
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:57,200
Thank you.

388
00:26:57,560 --> 00:26:58,560
Pae, you...

389
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:10,800
I'll head out first.

390
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:23,360
Now, get up.

391
00:27:56,320 --> 00:27:57,760
Your room still smells nice...

392
00:28:05,920 --> 00:28:08,360
♫Not every night brings sweet dreams♫

393
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:10,840
♫Flowers do not always bloom, you see♫

394
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:13,280
Go take a bath.

395
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:18,180
♫I don't know how it'll play out,♫

396
00:28:18,480 --> 00:28:20,680
♫But there's one thing I know,♫

397
00:28:21,800 --> 00:28:24,320
♫I have you right here with me♫

398
00:28:25,840 --> 00:28:28,080
♫If it's too heavy,♫

399
00:28:28,120 --> 00:28:30,400
♫You can lean on my shoulders, babe♫

400
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:33,080
♫I'm so fine♫

401
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:36,760
♫I'm lucky to have you here♫

402
00:28:36,800 --> 00:28:39,880
♫Oh, oh, oh, oh♫

403
00:28:40,240 --> 00:28:42,200
♫At least I've got you, so have no fear♫

404
00:28:42,240 --> 00:28:45,480
♫Oh, oh, oh, oh-oh♫

405
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:48,360
♫There might be ups and downs,♫

406
00:28:48,400 --> 00:28:50,800
♫Just the stars
pulling the strings around♫

407
00:28:50,840 --> 00:28:53,440
♫I guess it's still all fine♫

408
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:57,760
♫'Cause I've still got you by my side♫

409
00:28:58,880 --> 00:29:02,280
♫Oh, oh, oh, oh♫

410
00:29:03,760 --> 00:29:07,520
♫Oh, oh, oh, oh-oh♫

411
00:29:08,040 --> 00:29:10,480
♫Not the best but still good♫

412
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:13,240
♫I've got you here, so it all feels good♫

413
00:29:15,880 --> 00:29:18,880
♫I'm lucky to have you here♫

414
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:34,960
Pushing yourself through your limits.

415
00:29:35,600 --> 00:29:36,720
How stubborn.

416
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:07,120
Sheesh!

417
00:31:10,480 --> 00:31:12,600
Returned the storage room key for you.

418
00:31:12,860 --> 00:31:14,040
The work is done?

419
00:31:14,360 --> 00:31:15,640
Isn't that a good thing?

420
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:23,360
Jamie asked you to pick me up, didn't he?

421
00:31:24,540 --> 00:31:25,540
Go take a shower.

422
00:31:25,740 --> 00:31:26,560
We're going out.

423
00:31:27,440 --> 00:31:28,520
Where are we going?

424
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:30,280
Are you coming or not?

425
00:31:33,920 --> 00:31:35,200
Wherever you're taking me,

426
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:37,280
I'll be there with you!

427
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:40,440
Good.

428
00:31:42,600 --> 00:31:44,400
When you know you're at your limit,

429
00:31:44,840 --> 00:31:46,440
don't ever push through it again, alright?

430
00:31:47,320 --> 00:31:48,240
I'm worried about you.

431
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:54,600
Stawp, Qin!

432
00:31:54,800 --> 00:31:56,800
Don't play with my heart like that.

433
00:32:01,120 --> 00:32:02,200
Now, go take a shower.

434
00:32:02,320 --> 00:32:03,240
I have an outfit prepared for you.

435
00:32:03,840 --> 00:32:04,960
Sure thing.

436
00:33:14,920 --> 00:33:16,080
Did you just take me to your house?

437
00:33:17,040 --> 00:33:18,200
Well, it's not yours, is it?

438
00:33:19,660 --> 00:33:20,520
Ooh...

439
00:33:21,080 --> 00:33:22,400
What do your parents like?

440
00:33:22,440 --> 00:33:23,720
I didn't prepare myself at all,

441
00:33:23,760 --> 00:33:25,200
let alone any gifts.

442
00:33:25,440 --> 00:33:26,840
Let's go buy something first, then.

443
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:27,560
Come on.

444
00:33:31,800 --> 00:33:32,640
Are you done?

445
00:33:36,520 --> 00:33:38,720
My parents are just back home from abroad.

446
00:33:39,360 --> 00:33:40,360
They're free today,

447
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:42,600
so I want you to meet them.

448
00:33:46,680 --> 00:33:47,560
Are we going in?

449
00:33:48,880 --> 00:33:49,560
Yes.

450
00:33:50,580 --> 00:33:51,300
Come on.

451
00:34:08,400 --> 00:34:10,120
Qin, are you home?

452
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:20,199
I brought Duang with me today.

453
00:34:20,400 --> 00:34:22,080
- Hello.
- Hello, there.

454
00:34:22,679 --> 00:34:24,199
Have you two eaten?

455
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:27,440
We haven't, Auntie.

456
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:29,600
No need to call me Auntie.

457
00:34:29,639 --> 00:34:31,199
You can call me Mom, like Qin does.

458
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:32,320
Of course, Mom!

459
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:37,280
Right.

460
00:34:37,600 --> 00:34:39,719
Then, let's have a meal together.

461
00:34:39,760 --> 00:34:41,679
Dad even cooked today, Qin.

462
00:34:43,120 --> 00:34:43,920
Right, Mom.

463
00:34:45,199 --> 00:34:46,400
Duang doesn't eat Chinese Kale.

464
00:34:50,239 --> 00:34:52,440
You've said it in the calls so many times.

465
00:34:52,679 --> 00:34:53,679
I remember it.

466
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:55,480
Mom...

467
00:34:57,120 --> 00:34:58,400
Come on, let's eat.

468
00:35:04,200 --> 00:35:05,440
You're as pretty as your mom.

469
00:35:05,760 --> 00:35:06,560
Stop.

470
00:35:07,080 --> 00:35:09,520
Well, you really do look like her.

471
00:35:10,080 --> 00:35:11,280
Have you even seen my dad?

472
00:35:11,920 --> 00:35:13,480
Yeah... You're right.

473
00:35:19,240 --> 00:35:21,280
- There you go, honey.
- Thank you.

474
00:35:23,080 --> 00:35:23,880
Duang,

475
00:35:24,800 --> 00:35:25,760
don't be nervous.

476
00:35:26,600 --> 00:35:27,320
Alright.

477
00:35:32,840 --> 00:35:35,400
Duang, did you know
that you're the first one?

478
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:37,480
Qin's never brought anyone home before?

479
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:42,200
Uh...school's just been tough.

480
00:35:42,480 --> 00:35:43,680
That's not true.

481
00:35:43,840 --> 00:35:46,040
If that was the case,
you would have told me something.

482
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:47,400
You're very smart, after all.

483
00:35:47,440 --> 00:35:48,840
I don't believe you.

484
00:35:59,840 --> 00:36:00,520
Qin,

485
00:36:01,600 --> 00:36:03,040
do you find my cooking any good?

486
00:36:04,440 --> 00:36:05,280
I do.

487
00:36:06,400 --> 00:36:07,400
What about you, Duang?

488
00:36:09,320 --> 00:36:11,040
It's really good. Everything is.

489
00:36:11,080 --> 00:36:12,520
The fish is sweet,

490
00:36:12,720 --> 00:36:13,840
the shrimp are so, so fresh,

491
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:15,720
and every block of ice is nice and cold.

492
00:36:15,760 --> 00:36:16,920
I love everything.

493
00:36:18,480 --> 00:36:19,490
Do you believe it now, sweetie?

494
00:36:19,530 --> 00:36:20,810
- I do now, honey.
- Mm.

495
00:36:21,600 --> 00:36:24,000
Duang, you're a funny guy.

496
00:36:25,160 --> 00:36:26,160
That's nice.

497
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:28,320
Be the colors in Qin's life.

498
00:36:39,820 --> 00:36:40,880
Right, Qin.

499
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:44,320
Next week,
Mom and I are traveling to San Francisco.

500
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:46,840
You've been there four times already.

501
00:36:47,600 --> 00:36:49,160
Are you buying a house there?

502
00:36:52,840 --> 00:36:55,200
See, sweetie? I told you so.

503
00:36:55,240 --> 00:36:56,560
He's scolding you.

504
00:36:57,000 --> 00:36:57,960
I'm not.

505
00:36:58,280 --> 00:36:59,200
It's just a question.

506
00:37:01,040 --> 00:37:02,720
Well, the city's just my cup of tea.

507
00:37:05,280 --> 00:37:06,240
Have you ever been there, Duang?

508
00:37:06,940 --> 00:37:07,820
I haven't.

509
00:37:08,120 --> 00:37:09,240
We'll take a trip together later, then.

510
00:37:10,040 --> 00:37:11,600
Come with me, Mom,

511
00:37:11,640 --> 00:37:12,720
and Qin.

512
00:37:13,180 --> 00:37:15,000
Ask for your parents' permission
in advance.

513
00:37:15,200 --> 00:37:16,200
All you need to do is show up.

514
00:37:16,760 --> 00:37:17,600
Alright.

515
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:20,280
In that case...

516
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:22,120
give me some notice before the trip.

517
00:37:22,440 --> 00:37:24,160
I don't think I'll be home often.

518
00:37:25,600 --> 00:37:26,520
Sure thing.

519
00:37:33,760 --> 00:37:34,760
Here's a shrimp for you.

520
00:37:42,680 --> 00:37:45,920
I'm happy that
Qin's got you to take care of him, Duang.

521
00:37:49,640 --> 00:37:50,560
Of course.

522
00:37:50,600 --> 00:37:51,720
Me, too.

523
00:37:53,160 --> 00:37:55,160
Qin sure looks more lively.

524
00:38:00,960 --> 00:38:04,240
Boys, Mom and I
will go see a movie tonight.

525
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:06,800
Duang,

526
00:38:07,720 --> 00:38:09,720
can you spend the night here with Qin?

527
00:38:13,920 --> 00:38:16,760
So...I'm taking her to a romantic date,

528
00:38:17,120 --> 00:38:18,280
and it's a romance movie.

529
00:38:18,320 --> 00:38:20,840
It's probably...not Qin's style.

530
00:38:22,080 --> 00:38:22,720
Oh,

531
00:38:23,080 --> 00:38:23,640
really?

532
00:38:23,680 --> 00:38:25,960
- But for 'A Star Is Born,' he...
- It's alright.

533
00:38:28,280 --> 00:38:29,480
You two can go.

534
00:38:30,040 --> 00:38:31,120
I'll be fine.

535
00:38:31,720 --> 00:38:32,520
I'm used to it.

536
00:38:34,200 --> 00:38:35,160
Duang, are you okay with that?

537
00:38:35,640 --> 00:38:36,360
Yes,

538
00:38:36,960 --> 00:38:38,600
if it's not too much of a problem.

539
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:40,200
Not at all.

540
00:38:40,240 --> 00:38:41,440
It's my pleasure, really.

541
00:38:42,640 --> 00:38:44,520
You're like another son of mine, Duang.

542
00:38:45,640 --> 00:38:47,040
Please take care of him for me.

543
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:52,720
Qin,

544
00:38:53,040 --> 00:38:54,200
after the meal,

545
00:38:54,240 --> 00:38:57,240
can you...take a look at my guitar?

546
00:38:57,600 --> 00:38:58,720
I've never played it for so long,

547
00:38:58,760 --> 00:39:00,480
so I'm not sure if it's out of tune.

548
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:02,200
Of course.

549
00:39:16,320 --> 00:39:17,720
What classes are you studying right now?

550
00:39:19,540 --> 00:39:20,480
Well...

551
00:39:23,080 --> 00:39:24,680
Music stuff.

552
00:39:26,040 --> 00:39:28,480
I'm practicing with my friends as a band

553
00:39:28,520 --> 00:39:29,760
